I think theres two real dangerous elements to what they're using her to push.

First is food. They're trying to dramatically alter human diet. When you look at what they're pushing (vegan diets/insect protein) you quickly realise that this would cause considerable malnourishment among the general populace.
Even accounting for the protein sources that are available in this scenario, not all protein is created equal. And we'd be missing out on a host of other essential nutritional elements that would result in most of humanity becoming a lot dumber and weaker. 

High quality nutrition is a requirement for the creation of high quality humans. You can't cut corners here and meat has to be a hefty part of that intake. 
So it's no shock the upper classes want to limit nutrition quality for the masses. Makes them easier to control and less able to understand what is going on around them. If you want an example just look at the lower classes in our society who rely heavily on processed foods and fast food.

The second danger is the push for travel limitation.

Mass air travel especially has been the great equaliser in terms of travel. 
It has enabled the majority of the species to become able to travel the world increasing the capacity for communication between parts of the world. If you manage to control the internet and prevent the spread of wrongthink that way then you must inevitably also target mass travel as this will be the other way for wrongthink to spread.

There is also the added bonus that the more you limit travel the more captive a regions workforce is thus allowing you to more heavily exploit them. 

But perhaps most sinister of all is that a population who are in effect imprisoned in one area have little idea what is going on outside their corner of the world. Relying on media to tell them.
This would allow you to create a world with dramatically different standards of living without anyone except those at the top really realising. 
The majority of the population would live in a world of their own, ignorant of what goes on outside of it, forbidden from traveling to learn the truth and fed lies of the wider world by the media.

>>c4c94804-6593-4ae6-bef8-f464610c6ba3

Widespread education is great.
But end of the day our current methodologies aren't sufficient for the modern era.
We're past the point where industrialised schooling works, large classes listening to a single lecturer just ain't gonna cut it for actual education.
As it stands we rely on an innate knack for learning rather than cultivating it in those not born with it. 
In the past this was sufficient for the numbers of well educated people required, but now it's no longer sufficient especially with the universal franchise being a thing.

Unfortunately the classical model is not feasible at scale. 
It requires at a minimum a lot of one on one instruction by a primary tutor (typically a teacher of philosophy and/or natural sciences) who teaches the student how to learn and understand things like rhetoric. 
Then supplemented with access to a variety of other tutors in one on one or small group (half dozen or so) settings. 

This is so difficult to do that even among the ruling and owning classes only those at the top really have the means to pursue this method of education and is why they are able to consistently produce superior manpower.
